The paper focuses on ego-motion estimation for mobile robots, which is a core topic in robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method involves sensor fusion of lidar and IMU data, which is a common approach in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) for improving estimation accuracy. The paper also discusses the use of optimization algorithms to minimize cost functions, which is a common technique in control systems (cs.SY) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
